# Nimbus Design System - Cursor AI Rules

## Communication Language
- Always respond to user in español (Spanish)

## Code Standards
- **ALWAYS write code comments in English**
- **ALWAYS write JSDoc documentation in English**
- **ALWAYS write commit messages in English** (use conventional commits format)
- Always use English for variable names, function names, and identifiers
- Follow TypeScript strict mode
- Follow Nimbus component patterns

## Examples

### ✅ Correct Code Comments
```typescript
/**
 * Determines if the accordion item is interactive
 * @param interactive - Whether the item responds to clicks
 * @default true
 */
const AccordionItem: React.FC<AccordionItemProps> = ({
  interactive = true,
  ...
}) => {
  // Check if item should be rendered as static
  if (!interactive) {
    return <div>...</div>;
  }
  
  // Render interactive button
  return <button>...</button>;
};
```

### ❌ Incorrect Code Comments
```typescript
/**
 * Determina si el item del acordeón es interactivo
 * @param interactive - Si el item responde a clicks
 * @default true
 */
const AccordionItem: React.FC<AccordionItemProps> = ({
  interactive = true,
  ...
}) => {
  // Verificar si el item debe renderizarse como estático
  if (!interactive) {
    return <div>...</div>;
  }
  
  // Renderizar botón interactivo
  return <button>...</button>;
};
```

## Commit Message Format
```
feat(accordion): add interactive prop to AccordionItem
fix(button): resolve hover state issue
docs(readme): update installation instructions
```
